            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thank you for adding the file.\r\n\r\nThe list of envs is not very important to be up to date.  The most important part is the `[testenv]` section.  With the proper `[testenv]` I could simply run (the usual) `tox --current-env --no-provision --recreate -e py39`, instead of trying to find what is the proper way to run tests.  In case of Cython it is apparently `make test` which is extremely rare.  Even direct `pytest` run (which is another typical way to run tests without the `tox.init` file) does not work here.",
